<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2520: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice President of the Continental &amp;
                                    Commercial Trust &amp; Sowings Bank of Chicago</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Abbott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chicago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-01"><hi rend="italic">November 1,
                                        1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November
                                        1, 3.01 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your telegram October 31st received this a.m. We accede to your
                                request and will postpone at least temporarily the confirmation by
                                our executive committee of loan contract of October 20 and proceed
                                only to issue smaller loan contracted under agreement of October 11
                                for the redemption of funds maturing to-day.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jno. J.
                                Abbott</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>